abstract_ssm: The Jack Waters Papers contains information pertaining to downtown performance artist, filmmaker, writer, media activist and choreographer Jack Waters. The collection contains film elements from the 2001 preservation of three of his films under the supervision of Waters, the Fales Library, Jon Gartenberg, BB Optics, and the Estate Project for Artists With AIDS. In addition, the Jack Waters Papers contain a number of paper files pertaining to his various projects, such as writings, articles, and work with film festivals.
